rules: Rule1: Whenever legislation A is proposed, it is debated.
Rule2: In the event that legislation A is debated, then if skill Y is not available, legislation A is compliant.
Rule3: Provided that legislation A is implemented, it is enforced.
Rule4: If legislation A is controversial, then it is not the case that it is popular.
Rule5: Either legislation A is controversial, or if skill Y is not available, then drug X is not banned.
Rule6: If skill Y requires training, then drug X is approved.
Rule7: Provided that skill Y requires certification, it requires training.
Rule8: If drug Z is an alternative, then it is an approved alternative.
Rule9: Drug Z is an alternative or drug Z is experimental.
Rule10: If drug X is approved, then it is not the case that it is banned.
Rule11: Provided that drug Z is experimental, skill Y is available.
Rule12: If drug Z is an approved alternative, then drug X is tested.
Rule13: In the event that drug X is for emergency use, it is fast-tracked.
Rule14: Drug X is for emergency use or drug X has conditional approval.

Rule15: Either drug X has full approval, or if drug X has conditional approval, then if it is not the case that either drug X is tested or skill Y is available implies drug X is untested, drug X is not safe.
Rule16: Legislation A is reviewed or it is not the case that legislation A is implemented.
Rule17: Provided that legislation A is finalized, it is not reviewed.
Rule18: If legislation A requires skill, then whenever skill Y is not available, drug X is approved.
Rule19: In the event that drug X is unsafe, it is not safe.
Rule20: If it is not the case that if legislation A is controversial then it is popular, then legislation A is amended.
Rule21: Provided that it is not the case that either drug X is tested or skill Y is available implies drug X is untested, drug X is safe.
Rule22: If it is not the case that either drug X is tested or skill Y is available implies drug X is untested, then drug X is unsafe.
Rule23: If it is not the case that if skill Y is not available then legislation A is compliant implies legislation B is not compliant, then legislation B is enforced.
Rule24: Provided that it is not the case that if skill Y is not available then legislation A is compliant implies legislation B is not compliant, legislation B is not enforced.
Rule25: If it is not the case that if skill Y is not available then legislation A is compliant, then legislation B is compliant.
Rule26: If legislation A does not require skill, then legislation B requires skill.
Rule27: Provided that legislation A does not require skill, legislation B does not require skill.
Rule28: If skill Y is not available, then drug X is banned.
Rule29: Whenever skill Y is not available, legislation A is implemented.
Rule30: If skill Y is not available, then skill Y requires certification.
Rule31: If skill Y is not available, then it is not the case that legislation A is compliant.
